    "At larger fields the derivative develops strong oscillations, indicating the breakdown of the first-order Taylor expansion and the growing importance of higherorder terms as hoppings and intersite dipoles depend nonlinearly on E DC.It is instructive to compare the centrosymmetric 2H bilayer with the monolayer, as shown in Figure 5.",
    "The monolayer response is almost insensitive to E DC, while in the bilayer the same static field activates a strong and tunable σ (2).",
